definitions.definition: That which is produced or occurs as a result of an event or process.
examples: A quality automobile is the outcome of the work of skilled engineers and thousands of workers.

definitions.definition: The result of a random trial. An element of a sample space.
examples: Three is a possible outcome of tossing a six-sided die.

definitions.definition: The anticipated or desired results or evidence of a learning experience ( often used in the phrase learning outcomes ) .
examples: The outcomes of this course are outlined in your syllabus.

main_definition: That which is produced or occurs as a result of an event or process.
secondary_definitions: ( probability theory ) The result of a random trial. An element of a sample space.
( education ) The anticipated or desired results or evidence of a learning experience ( often used in the phrase learning outcomes ) .
( chiefly sports ) The scoreline ; the result .
